{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "lxxe:job.21",
    "translationId": "lxxe",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 21,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 21",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 21 in Brenton's English Septuagint."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.21.1",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:1",
      "text": "But Job answered and said,",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.21.2",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:2",
      "text": "Hear ye, hear ye my words, that I may not have this consolation from you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.21.3",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:3",
      "text": "Raise me, and I will speak; then ye shall not laugh me to scorn.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.21.4",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:4",
      "text": "What! is my reproof of man? and why should I not be angry?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.21.5",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:5",
      "text": "Look upon me, and wonder, laying your hand upon your cheek.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.21.6",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:6",
      "text": "For even when I remember, I am alarmed, and pains seize my flesh.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.21.7",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:7",
      "text": "Wherefore do the ungodly live, and grow old even in wealth?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.21.8",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:8",
      "text": "Their seed is according to their desire, and their children are in their sight.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.21.9",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:9",
      "text": "Their houses are prosperous, neither have they any where cause for fear, neither is there a scourge from the Lord upon them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.21.10",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:10",
      "text": "Their cow does not cast her calf, and their beast with young is safe, and does not miscarry.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.21.11",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:11",
      "text": "And they remain as an unfailing flock, and their children play before them, taking up the psaltery and harp;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.21.12",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:12",
      "text": "and they rejoice at the voice of a song.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.21.13",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:13",
      "text": "And they spend their days in wealth, and fall asleep in the rest of the grave.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.21.14",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:14",
      "text": "Yet such a man says to the Lord, Depart from me; I desire not to know thy ways.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.21.15",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:15",
      "text": "What is the Mighty One, that we should serve him? and what profit is there that we should approach him?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.21.16",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:16",
      "text": "For their good things were in their hands, but he regards not the works of the ungodly.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.21.17",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:17",
      "text": "Nevertheless, the lamp of the ungodly also shall be put out, and destruction shall come upon them, and pangs of vengeance shall seize them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.21.18",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:18",
      "text": "And they shall be as chaff before the wind, or as dust which the storm has taken up.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.21.19",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:19",
      "text": "Let his substance fail to supply his children: God shall recompense him, and he shall know it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.21.20",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:20",
      "text": "Let his eyes see his own destruction, and let him not be saved by the Lord.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.21.21",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:21",
      "text": "For his desire is in his house with him, and the number of his months has been suddenly cut off.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.21.22",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:22",
      "text": "Is it not the Lord who teaches understanding and knowledge? and does not he judge murders?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.21.23",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:23",
      "text": "One shall die in his perfect strength, and wholly at ease and prosperous;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.21.24",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:24",
      "text": "and his inwards are full of fat, and his marrow is diffused throughout him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.21.25",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:25",
      "text": "And another dies in bitterness of soul, not eating any good thing.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.21.26",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:26",
      "text": "But they lie down in the earth together, and corruption covers them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.21.27",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:27",
      "text": "So I know you, that ye presumptuously attack me:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.21.28",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:28",
      "text": "so that ye will say, Where is the house of the prince? and where is the covering of the tabernacles of the ungodly?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.21.29",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:29",
      "text": "Ask those that go by the way, and do not disown their tokens.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.21.30",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:30",
      "text": "For the wicked hastens to the day of destruction: they shall be led away for the day of his vengeance.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.21.31",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:31",
      "text": "Who will tell him his way to his face, whereas he has done it? who shall recompense him?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.21.32",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:32",
      "text": "And he has been led away to the tombs, and he has watched over the heaps.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.21.33",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:33",
      "text": "The stones of the valley have been sweet to him, and every man shall depart after him, and there are innumerable ones before him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.21.34",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:34",
      "text": "How then do ye comfort me in vain? whereas I have no rest from your molestation.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
